GIT : git is ntg but version control system/scm(source code management) tools.
VCS:
 * vcs is used in software industry where developer/teams to keep their source code changes at one place.(keeep the code and track the code )
 *tracking the changes had made to the source code with complete details (who,when,why).vcs can track text files and other file but except vedios and heavy quality images.
 *creating different versions when the changes had made to the code.
 *vcs allows you to switch(present and previous)versions of files.
 *source code is stored in repository(called as repo)
  *undo(retrive) changes when we required.
  *allow teams work on source code simultaneously.
